[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Stops mods from being unloaded when you return to the main menu, so you don't have to restart the game between play sessions.[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][b]Survives return-to-menu[/b] — without this mod, the game tears down plugin GameObjects when you quit to the main menu, leaving the next save load in a broken state.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Required by most other Sun Haven mods[/b] — almost every mod on my profile declares this as a hard dependency for that reason.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Bundled in the BepInEx Pack[/b] — already included in the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/sunhaven/mods/30]Sun Haven BepInEx Pack[/url], so if you used the pack to install BepInEx you don't need to install this separately.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Notes[/b][/size]

[size=3]Modders: call [code]KeepAlive.Plugin.AddGameObjectToNoKillList(myObject)[/code] from your plugin's [code]Awake[/code] to protect a custom GameObject from teardown on scene unload. The list survives across menu↔world transitions.[/size]

